cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of traffic allocation and load balancing in mobile edge caching, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also addresses optimization and algorithmic aspects, which could place it in categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses security and privacy concerns related to caching, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed algorithm using numerical and trace-driven simulations, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
